data.title: New Favorite Place!
data.text: Delicious salmon, filet, burgers, and salads. The shaved brussel sprout and kale salad is wonderful. Lovely view of Sundance Square and the fountains. During the week, the red umbrella valet service makes parking a breeze. Reasonable prices, nice servers, good music--it hits the spot!

data.title: Date night with my husband
data.text: We had a great meal. The atmosphere is a little busy and the bar was crowded on a Friday night but we had a great time. The cocktails are a little pricey like the menu but the drinks and meals were great. You get what you pay for

data.title: Was expecting better
data.text:
This was my first time dining at Del Frisco's Grill, we went there right after seeing a matinee show at Bass Hall (Phantom of the Opera), and were seated right away.  We started with the crabcake, which was very good, but for the price ($16), we should have noted it was only one.  Our server was Wendy who was very good without being overbearing.

My wife and I both got prime rib and it was flavorful, but not really any wow factor compared to other prime rib.  The horseradish sauce was good without being overly hot  Both of us also have the mashed potatoes, that were rather lumpy(?) 

I had the nutella bread pudding for dessert which was unique and very good, and not overly sweet like most desserts so my wife enjoyed it as well.

Overall, It was just an OK experience, we may be back to try the steaks, but for the price to quality ratio, we weren't overly impressed and may have been expecting more.  

It was an OK experience, may return to try

data.title: Nice Outdoor venue on Sundance Square
data.text: Great place to sit outside on Sundance Square. My husband and I both had filets. The steaks were tender, but a bit dry & not juicy at all. I had the potato pancake thing. It was cold & rather bland.  My husband had the mashed potatoes.  We liked them much better. They were mixed with green onion & garlic. We were there during happy hour, so some cocktails & wines were at reduced rate. Service was great, setting is great & I would definitely go back, but try something other than their steaks.

data.title: Great location
data.text:
Sundance Square offers plenty of choice restaurants for a weekend lunch. Del Frisco'a Grille proved to be just what we were looking for with its patio seating to allow for fun people watching. 
The steak salad was outstanding, the burger and fries were great. No mayo for the burger, but it wasn't needed. They do provide a special sauce if mustard isn't your thing, but you don't need to add it to the burger. Just get it on the side. The steak salad looks small, but looks are deceiving. No need for a steak knife since the steak is perfectly tender. The dressing is super tasty and the deviled eggs are outstanding. The tea is a little pricey at $3.50, but that tends to be the case at the pricier Sundance Square locations.
Del Frisco's Grille is NOT a place to try if you're looking for cheap eats. It's a medium priced restaurant with a varied menu offering something tasty for everyone.

data.title: Good Service, Ok Food.  Need more brunch options.
data.text: Food is good, but there is a lack of basic options for brunch.  Service was friendly and speedy since we were headed to a show.  The steak sandwich was dry and did not have a consistent flavor.  The crabs Benedict were excellent but could have used a side for the $.

data.title: Good but nothing special
data.text: We had various appetizers and salads. Everything was good but not exceptional. Maybe if we ordered something different ot would have been better.

data.title: Not your average Del Friscos
data.text:
I love Del Friscos, but must admit that the Del Friscos Grill in Ft Worth was not what I expected. It's not a Del Friscos Steakhouse. 
Great decor, service and wine list. But the menu is a mix of steak, meat loaf and sandwiches. 
I opted for the Ahi Tuna dinner, served on noodles sauced with a nice peanut sauce. 

The noodles were cold, which was fine, but were way undercooked. Al Dente x2

The Slices tuna was overly covered with sesame seeds. Way, way too many. I actually ended up slicing off all 4 edges of the tuna, so I could enjoy the fish, not seeds. 

Overall not bad at all, but don't think I will be returning on my next trip to Ft Worth.

data.title: Wonderful!
data.text: The weather was perfect, and we enjoyed our outdoor table on Sundance Square.  We had a very nice waitress (Serena, I believe).  The food was great!

data.title: Brunch
data.text: Excellent!!  The chef here has got their stuff together. We sampled a bunch of dishes as part of brunch and all were great.  The location was lovely. Sitting outside enjoying the vibe. Try the bao sliders, and the wings, and the crab eggs Benedict. Also their thick cut bacon. We will be back next time we're in Texas

data.title: A great Sundance Square restaurant
data.text: You can't go wrong with Del Frisco's Grille. It's one of my favorite places to take my relocation clients. My family also loves it. Food and ambiance are exceptional. Pretty views and outside seating is great for those with children.

data.title: Gouged
data.text: We went to del friscos with family for a special occasion. The food was good and the patio setting was nice. Upon receiving our check we were charged $94.00 for two shots of Don Julio 1942 tequila, being a tequila drinker I know the range for this tequila shot is from $15 to $25. The manager only offered the phrase "it is what it is". I wasn't asking for anything free just an explanation as to why they were gouging us. I called some of the bars in the area and the highest price for that exact shot was $25 and the lowest was $13. Lesson learned - ask before ordering tequila at Del Friscos.

data.title: You don't have to get a big steak here
data.text: I was on a solo trip to FW and went in for an early dinner.  I am a light eater while traveling and had a big lunch, so I ordered a bowl of soup (so good; the corn bisque) and a really yummy drink (adult chocolate thing).  Service was good and food was delicious; I definitely will return when in the area again.

data.title: Wife's birthday
data.text: Service was excellent. My steak was not tinder like Eddie Vs. Outback filet was better at less than 1/2 the price. Steaks were too salty for all 7 in the party. I was very disappointed since this was a premium steak house. I am not sure I would go here again. Appetizers were good.

data.title: Amazing Food & Friendly Service
data.text: We travel to downtown Fort Worth a few different times during the course of a year on business and Del Frisco's never disappoints.  The service is always top notch and the food is terrific.  You do want to be aware that the sides are served family style so if everybody gets multiple sides you may have too much food.  Also, if you are unsure about your wine choice, they have a sommelier on staff and they can prove to be quite helpful.  Lastly, if you do have a big group, call in advance and they will work with you to accommodate you, but just walking up with a big group can be a little challenging depending on the night.

data.title: Delicious Food and Wonderful Ambiance
data.text: The food and service here is always awesome. Highly recommend the deviled eggs and crab cakes on the appetizer menu. The staff is professional, helpful and always smiling. The view out onto the Sundance Square Plaza is beautiful and great for people watching while you eat. My only problem I have ever had there is on a few occasions the wait staff seem to disappear after the food is served. They might come back in a few minutes to check to make sure that we liked the food and it was cooked correctly, but I never see them again until check time. This means that I run out of something to drink halfway thru my meal and can't find them to refill. But this is a small thing out of an otherwise wonderful experience.

data.title: There is Sole in Ft. Worth
data.text: Del Frisco's Grille is upscale and has a great vibe. The food is delicious as are the drinks. The sole is the best we have had in years. The service is terrific.

data.title: Restaurant week grand slam
data.text:
We decided to try Del Frisco's Grille during restaurant week here in DFW. The menu was nicely varied. We chose the Cheese steak egg rolls and corn bisque for appetizers which were great! Those egg rolls are worth going back for! 
I chose the chicken entree and my boyfriend got the filet mignon, cooked medium rare, just as he asked. Both were delicious! 
The desserts we got were the chocolate cake and the butterscotch pudding with salted caramel topping. If I had to choose between the two, I don't think I could. They were both great. 
Service was attentive without being intrusive. Love the decor and ambiance of the place. Overall, a very positive experience and I would return without hesitation!

data.title: Business Dinner for 25 at Del Frisco's Grille
data.text: We had an incredible dinner at Del Frisco's Grille.  The food was excellent and the service excellent too.  We had a set menu since there were 25 of us.  I would recommend everything we had.  They started us out with ahi tacos and flatbread with sun dried tomatoes and pepperoni.  That was followed by the house salad with  2 thick strips of bacon on top.  The 3 main course options were filet mignon (which I had, which was cooked just right), parmesan-lemon sole and simply roasted chicken.  They served roasted asparagus and hand mashed potatoes with our entrees.  The desserts were perfect end courses.  We had lemon doberge cake (it was very moist) and warm chocolate cake with vanilla bean ice cream.  Everyone walked out full with big smiles on their faces.

data.title: Great Brunch!!
data.text: My best friends referred me to this fine establishment!! My sister told me about Banana Foster French Toast with thick sliced bacon. The thickness of bacon reminded me the bacon in Kuwait. I gives this 10 stars. My son had the chicken tenders. We all shared the cheese steak  egg rolls. They are delicious!!! 😘✌🏾️Lastly, I tried this called "The Morning After and The Tennessee Peach."
